@startuml
title Service Topology and Cost Comparison

skinparam backgroundColor #FFFFFF
skinparam shadowing false
skinparam defaultFontName Inter
skinparam defaultFontSize 14
skinparam defaultTextAlignment center

left to right direction

skinparam rectangle {
  RoundCorner 8
  BorderColor #1F2937
  FontColor #111827
}

skinparam arrow {
  Color #374151
  Thickness 1.5
}

skinparam note {
  BackgroundColor #F9FAFB
  BorderColor #9CA3AF
  FontColor #374151
}

' ===============================
' Traditional Architecture
' ===============================

rectangle #FEE2E2 "Traditional API Architecture\n\n\
Each service is a full custom build\n\n\
- Custom controllers\n\
- Embedded validation logic\n\
- Bespoke persistence\n\
- Duplicated infrastructure code" as TRAD

rectangle #E5E7EB "Service A\n(code only)" as A
rectangle #E5E7EB "Service B\n(code only)" as B
rectangle #E5E7EB "Service C\n(contract + code)" as C

TRAD --> A
TRAD --> B
TRAD --> C

note right of TRAD
Cost scales with number of services.
Architecture is reimplemented repeatedly.
end note

' ===============================
' New Architecture
' ===============================

rectangle #DCFCE7 "Contract-Driven API Architecture\n\n\
Single reusable runtime\n\n\
- Standardized persistence\n\
- Declarative validation\n\
- Enforced boundaries\n\
- One operational footprint" as NEW

rectangle #E0E7FF "Contract 1" as C1
rectangle #E0E7FF "Contract 2" as C2
rectangle #E0E7FF "Contract N" as CN

C1 --> NEW
C2 --> NEW
CN --> NEW

note bottom of NEW
Cost scales with contracts,
not with services.
New capability is primarily
a new contract.
end note

@enduml
